<subSubSection id="2CE85FE692F42709A5C45555A68519ED" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="36" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6934481314E159BFFD113D1881115DA5" pageId="36" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABB940494FB5D30889E090C529170496" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="36" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="3935699859FFDA152ADD1D2AB597EB7E" genus="Metallactus" lsidName="Metallactus" pageId="36" pageNumber="47" rank="genus">Metallactus</taxonomicName>
includes species that lack a deeply excised lateral edge of the elytra, additionally, the following characters may be useful to segregate species 
<pageBreakToken id="2CF61F68F9E682CAA2A232593858D533" pageId="37" pageNumber="48" start="start">into</pageBreakToken>
this genus: posterior margin of intercoxal prosternal process gradually narrowing, pointed; abdomen not exposed; elytral length greater than 2
<normalizedToken id="8561119E4BC1F856233EEE8DA7977945" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of pronotum (
<bibRefCitation id="E00AA8BB7ACB4DEFB386A70B4E8B52AC" author="Chamorro, ML" journalOrPublisher="Caucasian Entomological Bulletin" pageId="56" pageNumber="67" pagination="201 - 206" title="On the identity of Mastacanthus Suffrian, 1852 and Sternoglosus Suffrian, 1866 and key to world genera of Pachybrachina (Chrysomelidae: Cryptocephalinae: Cryptocephalini)." volume="9" year="2013">Chamorro 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BFC5971245BC5E5BD9E6DD2C3E6426E1" pageId="37" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
